One tip: if you want english breakfast or earl grey tea, don't order it from room service.	No announcement, explanation or apologies from the staff.	One morning, it took us 45 minutes to get silverware to go with our breakfast.	We opted not to pay the $27 parking fee (outrageous, I know) but instead found closeby metered spots.	I didn't try the Dragonfish, but did order room service which was well priced (for room service anyhow) and was up in 10 minutes.	You have to give a $50 daily deposit in case you use room service etc.	Upon checkout, we had to ask, for the third time, to have the breakfast charges removed.